6}$ erg. The outflows\nextend to radial distances of $r \\approx 0.1 - 3$ kpc from the nucleus, with\nthe gas masses, outflow energetics, and radial extents positively correlated\nwith AGN luminosity. The outflow rates are consistent with in-situ ionization\nand acceleration where gas is radiatively driven at multiple radii. These\nradial variations indicate that spatially-resolved observations are essential\nfor localizing AGN feedback and determining the most accurate outflow\nparameters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Jan 2021 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Apr 2021 15:11:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-22"}
